===Etymology===
The word "fusel" comes from {{etyl|de|en}} {{term|Fusel|lang=de}}, which is used to refer to low-quality alcoholic beverages in general, especially to inferior wines and spirits distilled with inadequate equipment.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|head=[[fusel]] [[oil]]}}

# A mixture of several higher-order [[alcohol|alcohols]] (alcohols with more than two carbon atoms) formed as [[byproduct]] in the normal [[fermentation]] process.  An excessive concentration, as in low-quality [[moonshine]], causes unpleasant taste.
